    <definition xml:id="definition-TI8assympint">
        <p>For a function <m>f(x)</m> with a vertical asymptote at <m>x=b</m> and a constant <m>c</m>, we let <m>\displaystyle \int_c^b f(x) dx</m> denote <me>\int_c^b f(x) dx=\lim_{a\to b^{-}}\left( \int_c^a f(x) dx\right).</me></p>
        <p>Similarly, <me>\int_{b}^c f(x) dx=\lim_{a\to b^{+}}\left( \int_a^c f(x) dx\right).</me></p>
    </definition>
